   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Message Twelve The New Jerusalem</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>the Ultimate Consummation</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>4</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The Triune God as Our Enjoyment,</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Living, and Expression Scripture Reading: Rev 21:11, 18-21, 23-25;</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>22:1-2, 5, 14, 19 The Triune God the Father as the light of life, the Son as the tree of life, and the Spirit as the river of life is the triune enjoyment of the New Jerusalem cf.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Psa 36:8-9: God as the light shines from within the Lamb as the lamp through the New Jerusalem as the diffuser Rev 21:23-25, 11; 22:5: We need to keep our heart pure and single for God so that our whole inner being will be illuminated, full of light without any dark part Matt 5:8; 6:22-23; Luke 11:34-36.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>For the building up of the Body of Christ, we need to walk and live under the divine, redeeming, shining light through the word of God Isa 50:10-11; 1 John 1:5-7; Psa 119:105, 130; Rom 13:11-14.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>We need to shine as luminaries in the world, letting our light shine before men in all goodness, righteousness, and truth for His glory Phil 2:15; Matt 5:14-16; Eph 5:8-9, 14; Isa 58:7-8; 60:1-5.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>We need to be one with Christ as the light of the Gentiles so that His salvation might reach to the end of the earth for Him to come again as the Desire of all the nations Acts 13:46-47; Eph 3:9; Hag 2:7; Matt 24:14.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The enjoyment of Christ as the tree of life will be the eternal portion of all God s redeemed Rev 22:14: The tree of life signifies God as life to man and declares that God offers Himself to man in an edible form Gen 2:9; John 6:35, 57; Rev 2:7.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>We are not only the eaters of this tree, enjoying the continually fresh fruit, but also the branches of this tree, abiding in Him to enjoy the life-juice Rev 22:2; John 15:5.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The river of water of life is the flowing out of the Triune God the Spirit as the ultimate consummation of the processed Triune God reaching His redeemed people for their enjoyment Rev 22:1: To contact God the Spirit with our spirit is to drink of the living water, which is to render real worship to God John 4:10, 14, 24; Isa 12:2-6.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>By drinking the living water, we become the New Jerusalem, the totality of the eternal life, the destination of the flowing Triune God John 4:14b.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The Triune God the Father as the source of life, the Son as the tree of life, and the Spirit as the flow of life is the triune living of the New Jerusalem Rev 22:1-2: We need to live out the Father as the source of life on the throne John 5:26: We need to take God the Father as our source with His redeeming element and with the element of His divine authority so that we may enjoy the flow of life for our organic salvation Rev 22:1; Rom 5:10.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>We need to live out the Father as love and as light by keeping ourselves in the fellowship of the divine life, the inner flow of the divine life 1 John 4:8, 16; 1:5, 2-3.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>We need to live out the Son as the life and life supply, the tree of life Rev 22:2; 2:7; John 14:6: We need to learn to take Christ as everything for His magnification Phil 1:19-21a; 2:5; 3:8-9, 13-14, 20-21; 4:8, 11-13.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>We need to call upon His name to enjoy His riches as our supply Rom 10:12; Phil 1:19; S. S. 1:3.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>We need to live out the Spirit as the bountiful supply of the processed and consummated Triune God, the flow of life Rev 22:1; Phil 1:19: The flow of the river of water of life in the New Jerusalem illustrates the fellowship of life, which is the flow of the eternal life within the believers 1 John 1:2-4; 1 Cor 1:9; 12:24; Rev 22:1.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The flow of the river of water of life is the one stream of the Lord s work for His one move through His one ministry to produce and build up His one Body for His one testimony Rev 22:1; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>1 Cor 16:10; 4:17; Acts 2:42.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The Triune God the Father as the source of the divine riches, the Son as the embodiment of the divine riches, and the Spirit as the realization of the divine riches is the triune expression of the New Jerusalem Rev 21:18-21; 22:1-2: The expression of God the Father as the source of the divine riches is His communicable glory in His rich life 21:11, 21: The first layer of the wall s foundation and the entire wall is built of jasper, signifying that the whole city bears the appearance of God for God s glory, His corporate expression vv.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>18, 11; 4:3a.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The work of the apostles, who are signified by the twelve foundations, is layer upon layer and leads to the unique appearance of jasper, the appearance of God in Christ 21:14, 19-20.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The expression of God the Son as the embodiment of the divine riches is in His person and with His work: The Lamb as the redeeming person is the lamp for the expression of God as the light through the city as the light-bearer to express Himself as the glory 22:5; 21:23, 11.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>The work of Christ s death and resurrection, signified by the pearls v. 21 , is a double cure that saves us from the guilt of sin through His blood and from the power of sin in His life John 19:34; Hymns, #1058 first stanza . The expression of God the Spirit as the realization of the divine riches is in His all-inclusiveness as the consummation of the processed Triune God: The all-inclusive Spirit as the river of water of life flows with God, with the Lamb, with the throne, with the divine nature as the divine way, and with all the unsearchable riches of Christ to saturate our entire being Rev 22:1-2, 17.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>The Christian life must be a life in the Spirit, by the Spirit, and with the Spirit, issuing in the fruit of the Spirit, with all the divine attributes expressed in human virtues Gal 5:16, 22-23, 25.</S>
   </TEXT>
